http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/Foreign-tourists-get-a-taste-of-Pongal-flavour/article14001312.ece

Thiruvalanthurai was abuzz with cultural activities on Thursday as the village played host to a group of foreign tourists to showcase Pongal festivities.A group of about 25 foreign tourists from France, the U.S., and Spain were treated to a lavish traditional reception and cultural show as part of a Pongal tourism festival got up by the departments of Tourism, Information and Public Relations, the Mahalir Thittam, and other government agencies.The tourists were accorded a traditional welcome with nadaswaram and thavil music, which was followed by folk dances such as Karagattam and Mayilattam.The tourists participated in the Pongal making ceremony at the thatched roof houses in the village.Rural youth gave an exhibition of traditional rural sports such as kabbadi, uriadi, vazhukku maram and tug-of-war. Before winding up the show, the tourists were taken around the village on bullock-carts.District Collector Darez Ahamed and Superintendent of Police Sonal Chandra were present.